      "pageid": 19894,
      "revid": 135636,
      "text": {
        "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>Find all pairs of rational numbers <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/8/e/8/8e8da0aef2d19017da7471378386d61620f288f5.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(a,b)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"38\" height=\"18\" /> such that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/6/1/9611a10934d20932453450ad8990985b21a1363e.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$0 &lt; a &lt; b$\" style=\"vertical-align: 0px\" width=\"75\" height=\"13\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/5/a/d/5ad20bc3e1a24c1d43385c0f5dcc28f7439a0d06.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$a^a = b^b$\" width=\"55\" height=\"15\" />.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Solution_1\">Solution 1</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=2020_USAMTS_Round_1_Problems/Problem_5&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Solution 1\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>We claim that there is only one solution, which is the solution pair <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/0/8/3/083dbaa4502f14028fd4f826e3ea1d1cb424d22d.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(a,b)=(\\frac{1}{4},\\frac{1}{2})$\" style=\"vertical-align: -13px\" width=\"110\" height=\"37\" />.\n</p><p>Let <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/8/3/8/83886fcd961361324a27bdb12f79d76b02c245ba.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$b=ta$\" width=\"48\" height=\"12\" />, where <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/0/d/e0d2bf360290fd61d1c1557e763f2622363b3d35.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$t$\" width=\"6\" height=\"11\" /> is a rational number greater than <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/d/c/e/dce34f4dfb2406144304ad0d6106c5382ddd1446.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"11\" height=\"14\" />. Then when we substitute that into the equation <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/5/a/45a638a87335392d89a8aeea2b7004ffefe2e574.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$a^a=b^b$\" width=\"55\" height=\"15\" />, we get <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/2/1/0/2100388a10480795c3a25d4a7d68f02a30075ad4.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$a^a={ta}^{ta}$\" width=\"70\" height=\"15\" />. We want to separate the variables from each other, so we can multiply by <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/0/d/a0dbfa28bcb1b0f91a6cab22d10ac26c25818e33.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\frac{1}{a}$\" style=\"vertical-align: -13px\" width=\"15\" height=\"38\" /> to get <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/2/8/328af1ad5ff4e43f35a20526d3db2feff32e03ca.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$a={ta}^t \\implies a = t^t \\cdot a^t$\" style=\"vertical-align: 0px\" width=\"179\" height=\"15\" />. Moving <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/c/7/d/c7d457e388298246adb06c587bccd419ea67f7e8.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$a$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"11\" height=\"10\" /> to the other side, and using the exponent rule, we get <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/0/1/9/0196fa5e7fb6bdb1938355039a556840e947f4cd.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$a^{1-t}=t^t$\" width=\"67\" height=\"15\" />. Multiplying this by <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/d/3/3d3ee003af1870ef986821aef515c833b48a25a6.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\frac{1}{1-t}$\" style=\"vertical-align: -13px\" width=\"40\" height=\"37\" />, we get <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/f/5/2/f52555e3a3766b6dfe48ee6499123dba623f194a.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$a=t^{\\frac{t}{1-t}}$\" width=\"62\" height=\"17\" />. Substituting that into <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/8/3/8/83886fcd961361324a27bdb12f79d76b02c245ba.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$b=ta$\" width=\"48\" height=\"12\" />, we get <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/0/b/7/0b7a5c351845e3f83bbb7d38b5168e3aff93afde.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$b=t \\cdot t^{\\frac{t}{1-t}}$\" width=\"80\" height=\"17\" />, so <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/f/8/6/f863bc83274f6a8b70b770076b789ce04cedb034.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$b=t^{\\frac{1}{1-t}}$\" width=\"60\" height=\"18\" />. Therefore our solution set is <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/8/2/4/824ec7bd58854855c8bb631ee23a913af9748bc5.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(t^{\\frac{t}{1-t}},t^{\\frac{1}{1-t}}$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"74\" height=\"22\" />, but wait! The solution set contains irrational numbers, and the question only asks for rational numbers. Therefore, <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/e/e/eee3f694b31c88634e4c9e15428daf8fe4cafb85.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\frac{t}{1-t}$\" style=\"vertical-align: -13px\" width=\"40\" height=\"37\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/d/3/3d3ee003af1870ef986821aef515c833b48a25a6.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\frac{1}{1-t}$\" style=\"vertical-align: -13px\" width=\"40\" height=\"37\" /> both need to be integers. By inspection, we can see that the only solution is <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/8/0/d/80d4822fd227ceb0ef72b1bd9326703a98f8593c.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$t=2$\" width=\"39\" height=\"12\" />, giving us the solution set <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/d/f/c/dfc515a31fca3c4ccaf7308b9f508a46230c56f3.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(\\frac{1}{4},\\frac{1}{2})$\" style=\"vertical-align: -13px\" width=\"47\" height=\"37\" />.\n</p><p>Solution and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/latex.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\LaTeX$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"46\" height=\"15\" /> by smartguy888\n</p><p>The problems on this page are copyrighted by the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.maa.org\">Mathematical Association of America</a>'s <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://maa.org/student-programs/amc/\">American Mathematics Competitions</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/File:AMC_logo.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"AMC logo.png\" src=\"https://wiki-images.artofproblemsolving.com//8/8b/AMC_logo.png\" width=\"97\" height=\"84\" style=\"vertical-align: middle\" /></a>\n</p>\n<div style=\"clear:both;\"></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240908055759\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.049 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.151 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 96/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 500/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 243/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 4058/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    1.476      1 Template:MAA_Notice\n100.00%    1.476      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key wiki-wiki_:pcache:idhash:19894-0!canonical and timestamp 20240908055759 and revision id 135636\n -->\n"
